<subSubSection id="C360656BFF97E53CD6D5FED1D0854715" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" type="key">
<keyStep id="308E2E45FF97E53CD6D5FED1D085455C" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FED1D09A457E" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" box="[181,1424,255,275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FED1D09A457E" box="[181,1424,255,275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">1a. Four neuromasts on caudal-fin base; horizontal golden lines present on caudal fin in males..........................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FECCD085455C" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" box="[181,1423,285,304]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FECCD085455C" box="[181,1423,285,304]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">1b. Two neuromasts on caudal-fin base; horizontal golden lines never present on caudal fin in males..................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308E2E45FF97E53CD6D5FEEBD09A458C" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FEEBD09A45EB" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FEEBD09A45EB" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
2a. Two dark-red stripes along entire dorsal and ventral submarginal parts of caudal fin in males; male caudal-fin stripes branching posteriorly; dark-red to dark-brown short transverse bars on basal portion of dorsal fin in males; three or four lateral mandibular neuromasts.................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF97E53CD283FEA4D09A45EB" authorityName="Cruz" authorityYear="1974" box="[1251,1424,373,391]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Cynolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aureoguttatus">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF97E53CD283FEA4D09A45EB" box="[1251,1424,373,391]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">L. aureoguttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FE43D09A458C" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FE43D09A458C" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
2b. Two dark-red stripes on anterior portion of dorsal and ventral submarginal parts of caudal fin in males; male caudal-fin stripes not branching posteriorly; dark-orange small spots on basal portion of dorsal fin in males; five or six lateral mandibular neuromasts................................................................... 
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF97E53CD2EEFE1CD09A458C" bold="true" box="[1166,1424,460,480]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF97E53CD2EEFE1CD03945B3" authority="Costa, 2008" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2008" box="[1166,1331,460,480]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="itanhaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF97E53CD2EEFE1CD03945B3" bold="true" box="[1166,1331,460,480]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">L. itanhaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23D5789FF97E53CD35AFE1CD09A458C" box="[1338,1424,461,480]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308E2E45FF97E53CD6D5FE3BD09A4676" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FE3BD0854591" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" box="[181,1423,490,509]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FE3BD0854591" box="[181,1423,490,509]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">3a. Dorsal-fin origin in vertical between base of seventh and ninth anal-fin rays; iris bright green in males.........4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FDD6D09A4676" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" box="[181,1424,519,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FDD6D09A4676" box="[181,1424,519,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">3b. Dorsal-fin origin in vertical between base of second and sixth anal-fin rays; iris bright blue in males ............ 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308E2E45FF97E53CD6D5FDF5D08546E3" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FDF5D09A4638" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FDF5D09A4638" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
4a. Caudal fin elliptical; dark-red stripe on distal margins of dorsal and anal fins, and dorsal and ventral margin of caudal fin in males........................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF97E53CD367FD93D09A4638" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[1287,1424,577,596]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opalescens">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF97E53CD367FD93D09A4638" box="[1287,1424,577,596]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">L. opalescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FD8ED08546E3" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FD8ED08546E3" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
4b. Caudal fin lanceolate; diffuse dark-reddish brown pigmentation on distal margins of dorsal and anal fins, and dorsal and ventral margin of caudal fin in males ................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF97E53CD292FDACD08546E3" baseAuthorityName="Costa, Lacerda &amp; Tanizaki" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[1266,1423,637,655]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="citrinipinnis">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF97E53CD292FDACD08546E3" box="[1266,1423,637,655]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">L. citrinipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308E2E45FF97E53CD6D5FD48D0854715" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FD48D085474D" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FD48D085474D" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
5a. Caudal fin asymmetrical, with convex dorsal outline and straight ventral profile; urogenital papilla attached to anal fin in males; anterior portion of anal fin with thickened tissue in males; caudal fin light blue with small dark-reddish brown spots, and white stripe with narrow black border on ventral edge of fin in males; flank dark brown with horizontal rows of yellow spots, coalesced to form stripe on the lateral midline of caudal peduncle in males .......................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF97E53CD292FCDED085474D" authorityName="Ladiges" authorityYear="1934" box="[1266,1423,783,801]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Cynopoecilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF97E53CD292FCDED085474D" box="[1266,1423,783,801]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">L. marmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF97E53CD6D5FCFDD0854715" blockId="3.[181,1424,216,890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead id="308B95D5FF97E53CD6D5FCFDD0854715" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">
5b. Caudal fin symmetrical, dorsal and ventral outlines convex; urogenital papilla free in males; no thickened tissue on anal fin; caudal fin red with light-blue vermiculate marks; flank red with zigzag-shaped bright-blue bars ...................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF97E53CD36EFCB6D0854715" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[1294,1423,870,889]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF97E53CD36EFCB6D0854715" box="[1294,1423,870,889]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="150">L. splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
